1 (2) the Secretary of Transportation or designee;
2 (3) the Commissioner for Children and Families or designee;
3 (4) the Commissioner of Financial Regulation or designee;
4 (5) the Attorney General or designee;
5 (6) the Managing Director of the Vermont Vehicle and Automotive
6 Distributors Association or designee; and
7 (7) a member appointed by Vermont Legal Aid.
8 (c) Powers and duties. The Committee shall examine the possibility of
9 amending Vermont’s laws to permit persons to cancel or rescind the purchase
10 of a motor vehicle under certain circumstances, including the following issues:
11 (1) the legal rights for motor vehicle purchasers in Vermont to:
12 (A) return a motor vehicle after it has been purchased and the
13 purchaser has taken possession of the vehicle; and
14 (B) cancel a contract to purchase a motor vehicle prior to delivery of
15 the vehicle;
16 (2) potential changes to Vermont’s statutes to permit a motor vehicle
17 purchaser to:
18 (A) return a motor vehicle after it has been purchased and the
19 purchaser has taken possession of the vehicle; and
20 (B) cancel a contract to purchase a motor vehicle prior to delivery of
21 the vehicle; and
