4 (d) Assistance. The Committee shall have the administrative, technical,
5 and legal assistance of the Department of Motor Vehicles.
6 (e) Report. On or before January 15, 2026, the Committee shall submit a
7 written report to the House Committee on Transportation and the Senate
8 Committee on Transportation with its findings and any recommendations for
9 legislative action.
10 (f) Meetings.
11 (1) The Commissioner of Motor Vehicles shall call the first meeting of
12 the Committee to occur on or before September 1, 2025.
13 (2) The Commissioner of Motor Vehicles shall be the Chair of the
14 Committee.
15 (3) A majority of the membership shall constitute a quorum.
16 (4) The Committee shall cease to exist on February 15, 2026.
17 (g) Compensation and reimbursement. Members of the Committee who
18 are not otherwise compensated for their attendance at meetings shall be entitled
19 to per diem compensation and reimbursement of expenses as permitted under
20 32 V.S.A. § 1010 for not more than four meetings. These payments shall be
21 made from monies appropriated to Agency of Transportation.
